Commentary Text: Sam Curran to Conway, 1 run, has he taken it? Livingstone seems unsure and the umpires have sent it upstairs. Slower short ball outside off, Conway pulls in the air, well in front of deep midwicket. Livingstone gets into an awkward position after running in. He's sliding forward legs first, with his body trailing behind. The ball is dying on him, but he somehow grabs it close to the turf. Third umpire has made his decision. He reckons it's touched the ground

Commentary Text: Tushar Deshpande to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by (sub)Shaik Rasheed!! Such a big decision this. To be fair to the third ump, it was touch and go if a spike on the boot grazed the cushion, needed a magnifier on that. But we don't get one and the third ump feels the cushion hasn't moved, so he goes with CSK. The crowd see the OUT on the big screen and there's a collective roar that can be heard till T Nagar. It was the slower ball outside off, Jitesh Sharma skies the loft and Rasheed was well in at long-on when he took the catch but he slipped and the momentum of his feet took him ever so close to the cushions. He was not sure when he got up, it was referred and the third ump went with the fielder there. Another umpire could well have gone the other way. Such is the margins of this game. Jitesh Sharma c (sub)Shaik Rasheed b Tushar Deshpande 21(10) [4s-2 6s-1]
